    <text>
        <body>
            <pb facs="MSVIII70v"/>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="ababccdeddde">
                <lg type="stanza" n="1">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>The lake smiled sweetly, and the boy,</l>
                    <l>Who lay upon its border sleeping,</l>
                    <l>Dreamed that he plunged beneath with joy,</l>
                    <l>And heard a sound like billows beating,</l>
                    <l>Or like the angels hymns that rise,</l>
                    <l>From the high thrones of Paradise,</l>
                <pb facs="MSVIII71r"/>
                    <l>And, as he woke him from his sleep,</l>
                    <l>(The vision floats before him)</l>
                    <l>High oer his head the waters leap</l>
                    <l>And voices murmured from the deep.</l>
                    <l>&#x201C;I snatch the sleeper into sleep)</l>
                    <l>And whirl my white waves oer him.</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
